1) Install firebase locally     -> npm i firebase-tools -D
2) Login to firebase            -> node_modules/.bin/firebase login
3) Initialize firebase          -> node_modules/.bin/firebase init hosting
4) What do you want to use as your public directory? -> dist
5) Configure as a single-page app (rewrite all urls to /index.html)? -> Yes
6) Set up automatic builds and deploys with GitHub? -> node_modules
7) Initilaize emulators -> node_modules/.bin/firebase init emulators


=== Emulators Setup
? Which Firebase emulators do you want to set up? Press Space to select emulators, then Enter to confirm your choices. Hosting Emulator
? Which port do you want to use for the hosting emulator? 5033
? Would you like to enable the Emulator UI? Yes
? Which port do you want to use for the Emulator UI (leave empty to use any available port)? 
? Would you like to download the emulators now? Yes

8) Modify firebase.json with following config 

{
  "hosting": {
    "public": "dist",
    "ignore": [
      "firebase.json",
      "**/.*",
      "**/node_modules/**"
    ],
    "rewrites": [
      {
        "source": "**",
        "destination": "/index.html"
      }
    ]
  },
  "emulators": {
    "auth": {
      "port": 9099
    },
    "firestore": {
      "port": 8080
    },
    "hosting": {
      "port": 5033
    },
    "ui": {
      "enabled": true,
      "port": 4000
    },
    "singleProjectMode": true
  }
}

9) Start emulators -> node_modules/.bin/firebase emulators:start

10) Deploy to firebase -> node_modules/.bin/firebase deploy --only hosting

11) firebaserc (Consists project configuration) and firebase.json (Consists server configuration capabilities, Setup custom redirects)